RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 10 6F Dirt CR: 65. Waiver Maiden Claiming Purse 36000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Weight, 119 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KAYMUS chased the pace, made a bid near the half-mile pole, took the lead in the two path just inside the seven-sixteenths, shook clear at the five-sixteenths, responded well under a hand-ride into the final furlong, swapped back to her inside lead when given one pop of a right-handed crop at the sixteenth-pole and just held. MANGIA was hustled from the gate, tracked the pace on the outside, was asked while four then three wide on the turn, pursued the winner in the stretch, gained in the final sixteenth and missed while well clear for the place. MEL'S ANGEL was urged along at the rear, went two to three wide on the turn, came out some into upper stretch, moved in near the furlong marker and improved position. NIGERIA raced towards the back, angled from the rail to the four path on the turn, remained on her left lead while behind horses to the furlong marker then shifted out and missed the show. NO LAYUPS bumped with a foe at the start, was urged along on the outside, went five then four wide on the turn and lacked the needed response. SIX O THREE broke in and bumped with an opponent, was urged along towards the rear, went three then four wide on the turn, spun six wide into the stretch and was no factor. AWESOME GLO chased the early pace then dropped back, saved ground on the turn, turned into the stretch in the two path and failed to rally. KHALI'S STORM was urged along on the inside of a rival, went four then three wide on the turn and came up empty. DACTILOGRAFA was urged along off the pace, saved ground on the turn and failed to threaten. SOL EMPERATRIZ showed good speed and set the pace, lost the lead while along the rail early on the turn, dropped back at the five-sixteenths and tired. HIGH TRACK chased the early pace then dropped back, went two to three wide on the turn, was taken in hand off heels outside the quarter-pole, swung five wide into the stretch and had nothing left.
